1
00:00:02,077 --> 00:00:08,141
Śrīla Guru Mahārāj will say,
“How is it that the soul

2
00:00:08,141 --> 00:00:10,241
is chit by nature too, 
conscious …

3
00:00:10,281 --> 00:00:15,543
How can you go from the chit-jagat—
the spiritual world—

4
00:00:15,543 --> 00:00:17,712
and start experiencing
the objective world?

5
00:00:17,712 --> 00:00:21,264
[A Shadow Self of the Original Self]

6
00:00:21,264 --> 00:00:28,026
It can’t, it’s not just suddenly
that that will …

7
00:00:28,026 --> 00:00:30,832
that that capability
and capacity is there.

8
00:00:30,832 --> 00:00:35,987
So, we introduce this concept
chidābhās or chāyābhās, saying,

9
00:00:35,987 --> 00:00:43,195
“The mind, the ego,
intelligence, and senses

10
00:00:43,195 --> 00:00:48,697
are a shadow self 
of the original self.”

11
00:00:48,697 --> 00:00:51,736
That’s what it is.
Chāyā means ‘shadow’.

12
00:00:51,736 --> 00:00:57,503
Chāyābhās, chidābhās 
also means …

13
00:00:57,503 --> 00:01:02,928
ābhās means 
‘a semblance of something’.

14
00:01:02,928 --> 00:01:08,313
So, he’s saying, in this … 
it’s just like a glove, you could say.

15
00:01:08,313 --> 00:01:10,581
The glove—
you put a glove on your hand,

16
00:01:10,581 --> 00:01:13,023
and you can handle
certain things.

17
00:01:13,023 --> 00:01:16,932
Now we have 
a little more sophisticated

18
00:01:16,932 --> 00:01:19,992
so-called virtual reality.

19
00:01:19,992 --> 00:01:24,332
There’re some similarities there;

20
00:01:24,332 --> 00:01:27,407
virtual as oppose
to substantial.

21
00:01:27,407 --> 00:01:33,266
So, Śrīla Guru Mahārāj said,
“This shadow-like self,

22
00:01:33,266 --> 00:01:37,925
this shadow of the conscious self,
enveloping the jīva soul,

23
00:01:37,925 --> 00:01:43,163
allows it to navigate
the objective world.”

24
00:01:43,163 --> 00:01:46,388
So, we’re seeing
through these eyes,

25
00:01:46,388 --> 00:01:51,998
hearing, tasting,
touching, smelling, feeling.

26
00:01:53,368 --> 00:01:56,751
So, as I said, 
the good news is

27
00:01:56,751 --> 00:02:04,111
this is indicative 
of the soul’s innate position.

28
00:02:04,621 --> 00:02:10,237
Like, even in genetic engineering
we find that

29
00:02:10,237 --> 00:02:16,177
when they want to duplicate 
someone or something …

30
00:02:16,177 --> 00:02:22,305
Like, remember Dolly the sheep.
Gurudev said something like,

31
00:02:22,306 --> 00:02:26,915
“When they all become Dolly,
the world’s finished.” [Laughing]

32
00:02:26,915 --> 00:02:31,334
So, there was the first sheep,
genetically cloned sheep,

33
00:02:31,334 --> 00:02:34,034
they called her Dolly.

34
00:02:34,534 --> 00:02:36,591
But how did they do that?

35
00:02:36,591 --> 00:02:40,147
This is what the point
I mean to make.

36
00:02:40,147 --> 00:02:42,997
They get some
genetic material.

37
00:02:43,008 --> 00:02:49,265
Genetic material means
something very minute.

38
00:02:49,265 --> 00:02:53,715
This is the point
I mean to make.

39
00:02:53,715 --> 00:03:01,645
DNA on a very minuscule,

40
00:03:01,645 --> 00:03:09,619
on that plane that’s where 
the full identity is located.

41
00:03:09,619 --> 00:03:12,237
That’s what
I am trying to say.

42
00:03:12,237 --> 00:03:14,138
That’s what
we learn from this,

43
00:03:14,138 --> 00:03:20,083
is that identity, 
and I’m making a parallel here,

44
00:03:20,083 --> 00:03:26,238
that identity is located 
in an even subtler plane than that,

45
00:03:26,238 --> 00:03:32,998
but within that plane there is 
the full spectral range of sensual expression:

46
00:03:32,998 --> 00:03:37,989
seeing, hearing, tasting, 
touching, smelling, feeling.

47
00:03:37,999 --> 00:03:45,149
So, if this body is the biological
expression of the soul’s delusion,

48
00:03:45,175 --> 00:03:49,750
and it’s taking shape and myriads,
and millions of forms.

49
00:03:49,750 --> 00:03:53,471
jala-jā nava-lakṣāṇi sthāvarā
lakṣa-viṁśati

50
00:03:53,471 --> 00:03:57,851
kṛmayo rudra-saṅkhyakāḥ
(Padma Purāṇa)

51
00:03:57,851 --> 00:04:03,416
Just as you combine RGB
or red, yellow, blue.

52
00:04:03,416 --> 00:04:06,393
Three makes nine,

53
00:04:06,393 --> 00:04:08,529
makes eighty one,
eight point one,

54
00:04:08,529 --> 00:04:10,544
eight million four
hundred thousand,

55
00:04:10,544 --> 00:04:16,464
millions of varieties
of variations of life-forms

56
00:04:16,464 --> 00:04:21,413
based upon tama, raja, sattva—
ignorance, passion, goodness.

57
00:04:21,413 --> 00:04:28,337
Millions of variations of that
generate these varieties of life-forms.

58
00:04:28,342 --> 00:04:35,852
So, as the body is based
upon exploiting tendencies,

59
00:04:35,863 --> 00:04:39,804
when we withdraw from
the plane of exploitation

60
00:04:39,804 --> 00:04:45,484
and become activated
with dedicating tendency

61
00:04:45,494 --> 00:04:49,269
under the guidance 
of sādhu, śāstra, guru, Vaishnav,

62
00:04:49,269 --> 00:04:53,600
then the svarūp
that you mentioned,

63
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:57,158
it’s under construction.

64
00:04:57,158 --> 00:05:00,788
It’s based upon dedicating
tendencies.

65
00:05:00,788 --> 00:05:05,763
So, as you can have a body here
based upon the tendency to exploit,

66
00:05:05,763 --> 00:05:11,066
the spiritual form is based
upon the tendency to serve and dedicate.

67
00:05:11,286 --> 00:05:15,619
The senses, the mind, 
the intelligence, 
 

68
00:05:16,279 --> 00:05:22,039
according to Guru Mahārāj,
all shadow representations
 

69
00:05:22,039 --> 00:05:25,724
of the spiritual aspect 
of the same.

70
00:05:25,724 --> 00:05:27,851
So, in Bhagavad-gītā
we hear Kṛṣṇa’s saying,

71
00:05:27,851 --> 00:05:32,415
bhūmir āpo ’nalo vāyuḥ
khaṁ mano buddhir eva ca

72
00:05:32,415 --> 00:05:36,455
ahaṅkāra itīyaṁ me
bhinnā prakṛtir aṣṭadhā
[Bg: 7.4]

73
00:05:36,455 --> 00:05:40,819
“Earth, water, fire, air, ether, mind,
intelligence and ego,” said,

74
00:05:40,819 --> 00:05:48,168
“these are My inferior energy.”

75
00:05:48,168 --> 00:05:51,779
Then He said, “And that so:
mind, intelligence—inferior,

76
00:05:51,779 --> 00:05:54,069
and jīva-bhūta—

77
00:05:54,069 --> 00:05:58,225
apareyam itas tv anyāṁ
prakṛtiṁ viddhi me parām—
[Bg: 7.5]

78
00:05:58,235 --> 00:06:06,843
jīva is parā-prakṛti,
superior energy to all of those things.”

79
00:06:06,843 --> 00:06:12,272
So, that means the mundane mind,
the mundane intelligence,

80
00:06:12,272 --> 00:06:19,856
these mundane elements—
they are covering jīva.

81
00:06:20,056 --> 00:06:29,989
But jīva in her pristine glory has mind,
intelligence, senses—everything.

82
00:06:29,989 --> 00:06:33,236
And that we connect with them.
What are we told?

83
00:06:33,236 --> 00:06:38,556
hṛṣīkeṇa hṛṣīkeśa-sevanaṁ bhaktir ucyate
[Nārada-pañcarātra]

84
00:06:38,556 --> 00:06:44,591
By engaging the senses
in the service of Kṛṣṇa,

85
00:06:44,591 --> 00:06:52,915
that will awaken 
their natural serving tendency.

86
00:06:52,915 --> 00:06:57,631
So that the mundane aspect
gradually vanishes,

87
00:06:57,631 --> 00:07:00,165
diminishes and vanishes
all together,

88
00:07:00,165 --> 00:07:04,411
and the spiritual golden self
comes out.

